  "packageName": "@cubid/wagmi",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/wagmi`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nwagmi-based React helpers that adapt host wallet-provider flows onto\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/evm`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ".\n\n## When To Choose This Package\n\nUse "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/wagmi`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " when your app already uses wagmi and you want Cubid's\nReact-friendly provider adapters on top of the EVM package. Choose\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/evm`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " instead for non-wagmi or framework-neutral EVM flows.\n\n## Install\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\nnpm install @cubid/wagmi @cubid/evm wagmi viem @tanstack/react-query\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nThis package expects the host app to already provide its normal wagmi setup,\nincluding "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`WagmiProvider`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " and the TanStack Query client.\n\n## Registry Availability\n\n- npm: supported\n- JSR: not published by policy\n\n## API Reference\n\n- JSON reference: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/reference/api/wagmi.json`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- Package matrix: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../README.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Basic Usage\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```tsx\nimport { createCubidEvmClient } from \"@cubid/evm\"\nimport { useCubidWagmiAdapter } from \"@cubid/wagmi\"\n\nfunction WalletVerifier({\n  apiClient,\n}: {\n  apiClient: Parameters<typeof createCubidEvmClient>[0]\n}) {\n  const evmClient = createCubidEvmClient(apiClient)\n  const { adapter, isConnected } = useCubidWagmiAdapter()\n\n  return (\n    <button disabled={!isConnected} onClick={() => evmClient.connectWallet({ adapter })}>\n      Verify\n    </button>\n  )\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nThe package also exports "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`createCubidWagmiAdapter`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " for apps that want to wire\ntheir own wagmi actions into the Cubid EVM adapter surface without using the\nprovided hook.\n\nThis package does not create wallet keys, perform normal transaction signing,\noperate an MPC provider, or broadcast transactions. Host apps and their wagmi\nconnectors own those responsibilities."
    }
  ]
}
